issue.title: Fix bug for read when persist
issue.body:
### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Fix bug for read when persist.

### Why are the changes needed?

There are at least 2 conditions for this bug:
1. open FileInStream before persist, and read after persisted and blocks are evicted, the exception is one of the following:
1.1. UnavailableException: Block .* is unavailable in both Alluxio and UFS.
1.2. NotFoundException: BlockMeta not found for blockId
2. open FileInStream when TO_BE_PERSISTED, and read after persisted and blocks are evicted, the exception is:
2.1. NotFoundException: Failed to read from UFS

So, a new option for OpenFilePOptions is added, user can choose whether to refresh uristatus if IOException occurs in AlluxioFileInStream

### Does this PR introduce any user facing changes?

a new option named "updateURIStatusWhenRetry" is added to OpenFilePOptions

commits.message:
Add FUSE path read write locks

### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Add FUSE path read write locks

### Why are the changes needed?

Guarantee single FUSE node read-write concurrency. Only one write
happens at a time. Multiple reads can happen at the same time.

With Alluxio master based filesystem, file read/write concurrency can be
guaranteed by the Alluxio master. Alluxio master will make sure only one
write can succeed and do not allow reading while writing. This is shown
as the file status field (isCompleted=true/false).

But with UFS based file system, no read/write mode concurrency is
guaranteed.
The following behaviors may happen:
- concurrently modify the same file through multiple clients (Not
controlled by FUSE SDK, out of scope)
- reading while writing through multiple clients (Not controlled by FUSE
SDK, out of scope)
- concurrently modify the same file through one FUSE SDK client. May
cause file in chaos situation. Can be controlled by Fuse side lock (this
PR) or UFS side global lock (UfsBaseFileSystem level) or per UFS
fine-grained control.
- reading while writing through one FUSE SDK. May cause read incorrect
data e.g. file size incorrect. Same, can be controlled by locking

### Does this PR introduce any user facing changes?

NA

pull_request.body:
### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Add FUSE path read write locks

### Why are the changes needed?

Guarantee single FUSE node read-write concurrency. Only one write happens at a time. Multiple reads can happen at the same time.

With Alluxio master based filesystem, file read/write concurrency can be guaranteed by the Alluxio master. Alluxio master will make sure only one write can succeed and do not allow reading while writing. This is shown as the file status field (isCompleted=true/false).

But with UFS based file system, no read/write mode concurrency is guaranteed.
The following behaviors may happen:
- concurrently modify the same file through multiple clients (Not controlled by FUSE SDK, out of scope)
- reading while writing through multiple clients  (Not controlled by FUSE SDK, out of scope)
- concurrently modify the same file through one FUSE SDK client. May cause file in chaos situation. Can be controlled by Fuse side lock (this PR) or UFS side global lock (UfsBaseFileSystem level) or per UFS fine-grained control.
- reading while writing through one FUSE SDK. May cause read incorrect data e.g. file size incorrect. Same, can be controlled by locking

issue.title: Fix bug for read when persist
issue.body:
### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Fix bug for read when persist.

### Why are the changes needed?

There are at least 2 conditions for this bug:
1. open FileInStream before persist, and read after persisted and blocks are evicted, the exception is one of the following:
1.1. UnavailableException: Block .* is unavailable in both Alluxio and UFS.
1.2. NotFoundException: BlockMeta not found for blockId
2. open FileInStream when TO_BE_PERSISTED, and read after persisted and blocks are evicted, the exception is:
2.1. NotFoundException: Failed to read from UFS

So, a new option for OpenFilePOptions is added, user can choose whether to refresh uristatus if IOException occurs in AlluxioFileInStream

### Does this PR introduce any user facing changes?

a new option named "updateURIStatusWhenRetry" is added to OpenFilePOptions

commits.message:
Add FUSE path read write locks

### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Add FUSE path read write locks

### Why are the changes needed?

Guarantee single FUSE node read-write concurrency. Only one write
happens at a time. Multiple reads can happen at the same time.

With Alluxio master based filesystem, file read/write concurrency can be
guaranteed by the Alluxio master. Alluxio master will make sure only one
write can succeed and do not allow reading while writing. This is shown
as the file status field (isCompleted=true/false).

But with UFS based file system, no read/write mode concurrency is
guaranteed.
The following behaviors may happen:
- concurrently modify the same file through multiple clients (Not
controlled by FUSE SDK, out of scope)
- reading while writing through multiple clients (Not controlled by FUSE
SDK, out of scope)
- concurrently modify the same file through one FUSE SDK client. May
cause file in chaos situation. Can be controlled by Fuse side lock (this
PR) or UFS side global lock (UfsBaseFileSystem level) or per UFS
fine-grained control.
- reading while writing through one FUSE SDK. May cause read incorrect
data e.g. file size incorrect. Same, can be controlled by locking

### Does this PR introduce any user facing changes?

issue.title: Fix bug for read when persist
issue.body:
### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Fix bug for read when persist.

### Why are the changes needed?

There are at least 2 conditions for this bug:
1. open FileInStream before persist, and read after persisted and blocks are evicted, the exception is one of the following:
1.1. UnavailableException: Block .* is unavailable in both Alluxio and UFS.
1.2. NotFoundException: BlockMeta not found for blockId
2. open FileInStream when TO_BE_PERSISTED, and read after persisted and blocks are evicted, the exception is:
2.1. NotFoundException: Failed to read from UFS

So, a new option for OpenFilePOptions is added, user can choose whether to refresh uristatus if IOException occurs in AlluxioFileInStream

### Does this PR introduce any user facing changes?

a new option named "updateURIStatusWhenRetry" is added to OpenFilePOptions

commits.message:
Add FUSE path read write locks

### What changes are proposed in this pull request?

Add FUSE path read write locks

### Why are the changes needed?

Guarantee single FUSE node read-write concurrency. Only one write
happens at a time. Multiple reads can happen at the same time.

With Alluxio master based filesystem, file read/write concurrency can be
guaranteed by the Alluxio master. Alluxio master will make sure only one
write can succeed and do not allow reading while writing. This is shown
as the file status field (isCompleted=true/false).

But with UFS based file system, no read/write mode concurrency is
guaranteed.
The following behaviors may happen:
- concurrently modify the same file through multiple clients (Not
controlled by FUSE SDK, out of scope)
- reading while writing through multiple clients (Not controlled by FUSE
SDK, out of scope)
- concurrently modify the same file through one FUSE SDK client. May
cause file in chaos situation. Can be controlled by Fuse side lock (this
PR) or UFS side global lock (UfsBaseFileSystem level) or per UFS
fine-grained control.
- reading while writing through one FUSE SDK. May cause read incorrect
data e.g. file size incorrect. Same, can be controlled by locking

### Does this PR introduce any user facing changes?

NA

Add FUSE path read write locks

Guarantee single FUSE node read-write concurrency. Only one write happens at a time. Multiple reads can happen at the same time.

But with UFS based file system, no read/write mode concurrency is guaranteed.
The following behaviors may happen:
- concurrently modify the same file through multiple clients (Not controlled by FUSE SDK, out of scope)
- reading while writing through multiple clients  (Not controlled by FUSE SDK, out of scope)
- concurrently modify the same file through one FUSE SDK client. May cause file in chaos situation. Can be controlled by Fuse side lock (this PR) or UFS side global lock (UfsBaseFileSystem level) or per UFS fine-grained control.
- reading while writing through one FUSE SDK. May cause read incorrect data e.g. file size incorrect. Same, can be controlled by locking
